<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 03 at 7:45PM EST  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...PATCHY FREEZING DRIZZLE THROUGH LATE THIS EVENING...
Patchy freezing drizzle will be possible through late this
evening. This could cause a very light glaze of ice on untreated
and elevated surfaces, like bridges and overpasses. The patchy drizzle
and freezing drizzle will change over to snow showers during the
overnight with light snowfall accumulations possible by Thursday
morning. Temperatures will fall into the middle and upper 20s
later tonight. Any moisture that remains on untreated roadways
could freeze and cause a few slick spots for early Thursday
morning.
Slow down and allow extra time to reach your destination
this morning. Roads, bridges, and overpasses that just look wet
may be icy.</description>
